        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35628",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please give an example of what you want to archive.\r\nActually I just see problems with your change.\r\n\r\nRelated to Zend_Validate's translation there is already a resource file available which can be used.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-30T05:47:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-30T05:47:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35735",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Closing as incomplete as there is no response.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-02T12:22:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-02T12:22:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36051",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=scramatte",
                        "name": "scramatte",
                        "displayName": "S\u00e9bastien Cramatte",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What I mean is if you use any other \"Zend_Translate_Adapter_*\" than \"Zend_Translate_Adapter_Array\" you can't use constant like Zend_Validate_NotEmpty::IS_EMPTY to make your Zend_Validate translation. \r\n\r\nYou must put the exact string as specified in the source class: \r\nself::IS_EMPTY = \"Value is required and can't be empty\".\r\n\r\nIf for any reason somebody change this hardcoded string, form validation will not be translated properly. \r\n\r\nI've got a project that must translated in 5 languages and  it's fare easy to use constant in  translation data (in my case I use CSV adapter).\r\n\r\nExample (CSV file) :\r\n\r\n...\r\nZend_Validate_NotEmpty::IS_EMPTY;Cette valeur ne peut \u00eatre vide \r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=scramatte",
                        "name": "scramatte",
                        "displayName": "S\u00e9bastien Cramatte",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-17T00:40:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-17T00:41:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36089",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This would not work as expected.\r\nSee the following example:\r\n\r\nExpect this original:\r\nZend_Validate_File::EMPTY => 'file is empty'\r\n\r\nNow you do:\r\n\"Zend_Validate_File::EMPTY\";\"file is empty\"\r\n\r\nThen there is a change in the constant\r\n\r\nZend_Validate_File::EMPTY => 'file or directory is empty'\r\n\r\nBut as you set the translation by constant it would for you still return\r\n\"file is empty\".\r\n\r\nThis is not expected behaviour, it would even make more problems than getting an \"no translation warning\" which returns the original string.\r\n\r\nTherefor it is always better to have\r\n'file is empty'; 'translated text'\r\nas it prevents you from further problems. You would have to do a new translation in any case. But by allowing constants you would not know that anything has changed.\r\n\r\nAnd to prevent typing there are existing resource files which could be used.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-18T03:30:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-18T03:30:08.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
